    [acr('NGFS', 'Network for Greening the Financial System', 'Central bank network coordinating climate scenario development'), acr('BCBS', 'Basel Committee on Banking Supervision', 'Sets global banking prudential standards including BCBS 530 on climate'), acr('FSB', 'Financial Stability Board', 'G20 body coordinating global financial regulation including climate'), acr('SCR', 'Solvency Capital Requirement', 'Risk-based capital requirement for insurance companies'), acr('CCyB', 'Countercyclical Capital Buffer', 'Macroprudential tool that could be calibrated for climate risk')],
    [dl('NGFS scenario parameters', 'Sector shock transmission', 'Bank-level impact estimates'), dl('Supervisory data', 'Climate risk assessment', 'SREP climate score'), dl('Financial stability analysis', 'Macroprudential recommendation', 'Policy response tools')],
    'Central banks globally are integrating climate into supervisory frameworks. BCBS 530 principles, ECB climate risk management guide, BoE SS3/19, and NGFS membership create regulatory expectations for banks. This module provides the analytical framework for both regulated institutions and supervisors.'
