    [dl('Corporate network topology', 'Climate shock application', 'Initial default probabilities'), dl('Default probabilities', 'Contagion propagation', 'Cascade loss estimates'), dl('Network losses', 'Systemic risk quantification', 'Capital adequacy assessment')],
    'Climate-driven credit events are not independent — they hit sectors simultaneously and propagate through supply chain and financial networks. This module quantifies the systemic amplification of climate shocks, identifying which companies are cascade hubs requiring heightened supervisory attention.'
